<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Wed 3 Jul 2002
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Ontario Ministry of Health and Long Term Care, West Nile Virus
Bulletin, Wed 3 Jul 2002 [edited]
<http://www.gov.on.ca/health/english/program/pubhealth/wnv_mn.html>

Current status of West Nile virus in Ontario
--------------------------------------------
The Ministry of Health and Long-Term Care works with local public health
units and Health Canada to monitor the presence of West Nile virus (WNV) in
the province.
As of Wed 3 Jul 2002, 9 birds have been confirmed positive for WNV in
Ontario, as follows (species not given):
Peel Region, 1 confirmed (collected 19 May 2002);
Oxford Region, 1 confirmed (collected 4 Jun 2002);
Chatham-Kent Region, 5 confirmed (collected 12 to 14 Jun 2002;
Middlesex-London Region, 1 confirmed (collected 17 Jun 2002);
Halton Region, 1 confirmed (collected 15 Jun 2002).
The presence of West Nile virus in Canada was confirmed first on 22 Aug
2001 in a bird submitted from Windsor-Essex Country. Neither the virus nor
its symptoms have been detected in humans to date.
